The paper discusses the development of a scalable hypergraph processing system, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The system is designed to analyze large-scale social structures and behaviors, which could be categorized under social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the use of real datasets, which suggests a focus on database systems (cs.DB). The system is designed to be flexible and scalable, which could be categorized under systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the system, which could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves evaluating the effectiveness of a computational system.
